nd contemporary manifestations of racism in Canadian academic institutions, finding in these communities a deep rift between how racism is imagined and how it is lived.With equal emphasis on scholarship and personal perspectives, Racism in the Canadian University is an important look at how racial minority faculty and students continue to engage in a daily struggle for safe, inclusive spaces in classrooms and among peers, colleagues, and administrators.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aMinorities in higher educationzCanada. 0aRacism in higher educationzCanada. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh1 aDua, Enakshi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenry, Frances, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenry, Frances, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHernandez-Ramdwar, Camille, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJames, Carl E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKobayashi, Audrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMonture, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTator, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTator, Carol, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144268892640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442688926423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442688926.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK